{Album ratings\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{Allmusic|class=album|id=19095|title=Vagabond Heart \u2013 Rod Stewart|last=Erlewine|first=Stephen Thomas|authorlink=Stephen Thomas Erlewine|accessdate=2011-11-07}}</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]''\n| rev2score = B\u2212<ref name=\"EW_review\">{{cite journal|authorlink=Dave Marsh|first=Dave|last=Marsh|title=Vagabond Heart Review|url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,313900,00.html|journal=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=1991-04-05|accessdate=2011-11-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Rod Stewart \u2013 Vagabond Heart CD Album|url=http://www.cduniverse.com/productinfo.asp?pid=1100410&style=music|publisher=[[CD Universe]]|accessdate=2012-11-23}}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[Houston Chronicle]]''\n| rev3score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chron.com/CDA/archives/archive.mpl/1991_780043/rod-stewart-grows-up.html|title=Rod Stewart grows up|last=Racine|first=Martin|newspaper=[[Houston Chronicle]]|date=1991-04-28|accessdate=2011-11-07}}</ref>\n| rev4 = ''[[Los Angeles Times]]''\n| rev4score = {{Rating|2|5}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1991-04-07/entertainment/ca-132_1_rod-stewart|last=Willman|first=Chris|work=articles.latimes.com |publisher=Los Angeles Times|title= Stewart's 'Heart' Beats Without Conviction : ** ROD STEWART : \"Vagabond Heart\" :  Warner Bros.|date=1991-04-07|accessdate=2011-11-07}}</ref>\n| rev5 = ''[[The New York Times]]''\n| rev5score = (unfavourable)<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1991/06/16/arts/record-briefs-234691.html|title=RECORD BRIEFS|last=Browne|first=David|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|date=1991-06-16|accessdate=2011-11-07}}</ref>\n| rev6 = [[Robert Christgau]]\n| rev6score = {{Rating-Christgau|dud}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.robertchristgau.com/get_artist.php?name=rod+stewart|title=CG: Rod Stewart|last=Christgau|first=Robert|authorlink=Robert Christgau|publisher=RobertChristgau.com|accessdate=2012-11-23}}</ref>\n| rev7 = ''[[Rolling Stone]]''\n| rev7score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/vagabond-heart-19910516|title=Vagabond Heart|last=McLeese|first=Don|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=1991-05-16|accessdate=2012-11-23}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Vagabond Heart''''' is the 16th studio [[album]] by [[singer-songwriter]] [[Rod Stewart]], released in 1991. The album reached No. 10 in the US, and reached No. 2 in the UK. The album features five singles, among them a [[Cover version|cover]] of [[Robbie Robertson]]'s song \"[[Broken Arrow (Robbie Robertson song)|Broken Arrow]]\" (No. 20 in the US) and [[Van Morrison]]'s song \"[[Have I Told You Lately]]\", which would become a hit two years later (in a live version) and is Stewart's most recent top five solo hit in the US and the UK. The two biggest hits from the album were \"[[Rhythm of My Heart]]\" (No. 5 in the US) and \"[[The Motown Song]]\" (No. 10 in the US).\n\n==Reception==\nOverall, the album received positive reviews. According to ''[[Rolling Stone]]'', \"''Vagabond Heart'' finds Stewart rising to new challenges as both a songwriter and a singer. The strength of the songs and the depth of Stewart's conviction make this his most compelling work since the early 1970s.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-album-reviews/vagabond-heart-251867/|title=Vagabond Heart|first1=Don|last1=McLeese|first2=Don|last2=McLeese|date=16 May 1991|publisher=}}</ref>\n[[AllMusic]] claimed \"''Vagabond Heart'' is a stronger, more diverse album than its predecessor (''[[Out of Order (Rod Stewart album)|Out of Order]]''), featuring a more consistent set of songs.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/vagabond-heart-mw0000691766|title=Vagabond Heart - Rod Stewart - Songs, Reviews, Credits|website=AllMusic}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.barnesandnoble.com/w/vagabond-heart-rod-stewart/73412?ean=0075992630023|title=Vagabond Heart|first=Barnes &|last=Noble|website=Barnes & Noble}}</ref>\n\nThe \"Vagabond Heart Tour\" was made available on video in 1992, shot during a concert in [[Los Angeles]] on [[Valentine's Day]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/movies|title=Showtimes, reviews, trailers, news and more - MSN Movies|website=MSN}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column = Producer(s)\n\n| title1       = [[Rhythm of My Heart]]\n| writer1      = [[Marc Jordan]], [[John Capek]]\n| extra1       = [[Trevor Horn]]\n| length1      = 4:15\n\n| title2       = Rebel Heart\n| writer2      = Stewart, [[Jeff Golub]], Chuck Kentis, Carmine Rojas\n| extra2       = Rod Stewart, [[Bernard Edwards]]\n| length2      = 4:10\n\n| title3       = Broken Arrow\n| writer3      = [[Robbie Robertson]]\n| extra3       = [[Patrick Leonard]], [[Lenny Waronker]]{{ref|a|[a]}}\n| length3      = 4:26\n\n| title4       = [[It Takes Two (Marvin Gaye and Kim Weston song)|It Takes Two]]\n| writer4      = duet with [[Tina Turner]]) ([[William \"Mickey\" Stevenson]], [[Sylvia Moy]]\n| extra4       = Stewart, Edwards\n| length4      = 4:14\n\n| title5       = When a Man's in Love\n| writer5      = Stewart, Jeff Golub, Chuck Kentis, Carmine Rojas\n| extra5       = Stewart, Edwards\n| length5      = 5:34\n\n| title6       = [[You Are Everything]]\n| writer6      = [[Thom Bell]], [[Linda Creed]]\n| extra6       = Stewart, Edwards\n| length6      = 4:09\n\n| title7       = [[The Motown Song]]\n| writer7      = Larry John McNally\n| extra7       = [[Richard Perry]]\n| length7      = 4:00\n\n| title8       = Go Out Dancing\n| writer8      = Stewart, Jeff Golub, Chuck Kentis\n| extra8       = Stewart, Edwards\n| length8      = 4:20\n\n| title9       = No Holding Back\n| writer9      = Stewart, [[Jim Cregan]], Kevin Savigar\n| extra9       = Stewart, Edwards\n| length9      = 5:47\n\n| title10      = [[Have I Told You Lately]]\n| writer10     = [[Van Morrison]]\n| extra10      = Stewart, Edwards\n| length10     = 4:01\n\n| title11      = Moment of Glory\n| writer11     = Stewart, Jeff Golub, Chuck Kentis, Carmine Rojas\n| extra11      = Stewart, Edwards\n| length11     = 4:47\n\n| title12      = [[Downtown Train]]\n| writer12     = [[Tom Waits]]\n| extra12      = [[Trevor Horn]]\n| length12     = 4:41\n\n| title13      = [[This Old Heart of Mine (Is Weak For You)]]\n| writer13     = [[Holland-Dozier-Holland]], [[Sylvia Moy]]\n| extra13      = Edwards, Horn\n| length13     = 4:12\n\n| title14      = If Only\n| writer14     = Stewart, Jim Cregan, Kevin Savigar\n| extra14      = Stewart, Edwards\n| length14     = 4:56\n}}\n\n'''Notes'''\n* {{small|{{note|a|a}}}} signifies a co-producer\n*\"Downtown Train\" and \"This Old Heart of Mine (Is Weak For You) are omitted on cassette copies, as well as some CD versions.\n\n==Personnel==\n(Personnel for the 12-track version of the album, excluding the tracks \"Downtown Train\" and \"This Old Heart of Mine\")\n* \"Rebel Heart\", \"It Takes Two\", \"When a Man's in Love\", \"You are Everything\", \"Go Out Dancing\", \"No Holding Back\", \"Have I Told You Lately\", \"Moment of Glory\" and \"If Only\" arranged and produced by Rod Stewart and [[Bernard Edwards]].  Recorded by Steve MacMillan.  Mixed by Bernard Edwards and Steve Macmillan.  Recording and mix assisted by John Karpowich, Gil Morales and Bryant Arnett.\n**Roy Galloway, Luther Waters, The Waters Sisters, [[Angela Winbush]]: backing vocals; [[Jeff Golub]], [[Jim Cregan]], [[Waddy Wachtel]], [[Dann Huff]]: guitar; [[Carmine Rojas]], Bernard Edwards: bass guitar; Chuck Kentis: keyboards, programming; [[Kevin Savigar]]: keyboards; Rave Calmer, [[Tony Brock]]: drums; [[Paulinho da Costa]]: percussion; Saxophone on \"Go Out Dancing\" and \"Moment of Glory\" by Jimmy Roberts; String arrangements on \"When a Man's in Love\" and \"Have I Told You Lately\" by Bruce Miller.\n* \"Rhythm of My Heart\" produced by [[Trevor Horn]].  Recorded by Steve MacMillan.  Mixed by Steve MacMillan and Trevor Horn.\n**Joe Turano, [[John Batdorf]], Randel Crenshaw, Gary Falcone, Roger Freeland, Robert Jason, Arnold Stiefel, Lionel Conway, Garry Cook, Antony Arena: backing vocals; Robin Le Mesurier, [[Steve Lukather]]: guitar; Gary Taylor, Kevin Savigar, Richard Cottle: keyboards; Michael McNeil: [[accordion]]; Kevin Weed: [[bagpipes]]; [[Neil Stubenhaus]]: bass guitar; [[John Robinson (drummer)|John Robinson]]: drums, percussion; Gary Maughn: programming; Choir arranged and directed by Nick Strimple and Joe Turano; Strings arranged and conducted by Kevin Savigar.\n* \"Broken Arrow\" produced by [[Patrick Leonard]]; Co-produced by [[Lenny Waronker]].  Recorded and mixed by Jerry Jordan, with assistance by Marc Moreau.\n**Twinkle Schascle: backing vocals; [[Tim Pierce]]: guitars; Patrick Leonard: keyboards; [[Jimmy Johnson (bassist)|Jimmy Johnson]]: bass guitar; [[Jim Keltner]]: drums; [[Luis Conte]]: percussion\n* \"The Motown Song\" arranged by [[David Paich]]. Produced by Richard Perry.  Recorded and mixed by Steve MacMillan, with recording assistance by Dee Ross and Eric Anest; Additional engineering by Lee Granados, John Karpowich, Scott Ralston and Eric Rudd.\n**[[The Temptations]]: backing vocals; Steve Lukather, [[Paul Jackson Jr.]]: guitar; Khris Kellow: keyboard bass; David Paich: acoustic piano, [[Rhodes piano|Fender Rhodes]]; [[Steve Porcaro]]: synthesizer; Steve Lindsey: synthesizer, synth horns; [[Jeff Porcaro]]: drums; Chris Trujillo: percussion; Horns arranged by Steve Lindsey.\n\n===Additional credits===\n* Mastered by [[Stephen Marcussen]] at Precision Mastering (Hollywood, CA).\n* Production coordination: Malcolm Cullimore (tracks 1\u20136 & 8\u201312); Julie Larson (track 7).\n* Project manager: Nancy Poertner\n* Art direction: Jeri Heiden\n* Design: Eric Handel\n* Illustration: Ann Field\n* Photography: Randee St. Nicholas\n\n==Publishing==\n*\"Rhythm of My Heart\" copyright WB Music Corp./Jamm Music/Bibo Music Publishers.  \"Rebel Heart\", \"When a Man's in Love\" and \"Moment of Glory\" published by Rod Stewart (Intersong Music Admin.)/Cat in the Hat Music/Kentis Music/Malango Bro. \"Broken Arrow\" published by Medicine Hat Music.  \"It Takes Two\" published by Stone Agate Music Division.  \"You Are Everything\" published by Assorted Music/Bellboy Music/The Mighty Three Group.  \"The Motown Song\" published by Geffen Music/McNally Music Publishing/MCA Music Publishing.  \"Go Out Dancing\" published by Rod Stewart (Intersong Music Admin.)/Cat in the Hat Music/Kentis Music.  \"No Holding Back\" and \"If Only\" published by Rod Stewart (Intersong Music Admin.)/Almo Music Corp/Kevin Savigar Music/BMG Inc.  \"Have I Told You Lately\" published by PolyGram International Publishing, Inc.\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!Chart (1991)\n!Peak<br>position\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|[[ARIA Charts|Australian ARIA Album Chart]]<ref name=\"auchart\">{{cite web| title = australian-charts.com Rod Stewart \u2013 Vagabond Heart| publisher = [[Australian Recording Industry Association]]| url = http://australian-charts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Rod+Stewart&titel=Vagabond+Heart&cat=a|format=ASP| accessdate=2011-11-07}}</ref>\n|1\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Austrian Albums Chart<ref name=\"atchart\">{{cite web|title=austriancharts.at Rod Stewart \u2013 Vagabond Heart|work=Hung Medien|language=German|format=ASP|url=http://austriancharts.at/showitem.asp?interpret=Rod+Stewart&titel=Vagabond+Heart&cat=a|accessdate=2011-11-07}}</ref>\n|5\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|[[RPM (magazine)|Canadian Albums Chart]]<ref>[http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/rpm/028020-119.01-e.php?&file_num=nlc008388.1545&type=1&interval=20&PHPSESSID=mhe12pta2k83e08udtq66ot062 Library and Archives Canada.]  Retrieved 2011-11-07</ref>\n|2\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|[[MegaCharts|Dutch Albums Chart]]<ref name=\"nlchart\">{{cite web|title=dutchcharts.nl Rod Stewart \u2013 Vagabond Heart|publisher=[[MegaCharts]]|url=http://dut